                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.01 Foreign Control/38: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berne</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-02-13T13:00:00+01:00"
                            >February 13, 1931—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 13—10:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>22. Gilbert’s 29, February 12, 1931.<note n="31" xml:id="d699fn31">Not;
                        printed.</note> Sugimura<note n="32" xml:id="d699fn32">Y. Sugimura
                        (Japanese), Under Secretary General and Director of Political Section of the
                        League of Nations.</note> has addressed through me to Reber a formal
                    notification of the convocation of the meeting of the Liberian Committee at
                    London, February 26th. He adds informally that he will arrange for some of his
                    colleagues to be in London by February 23 in order to have preliminary talks
                    with Reber. Reber’s notification forwarded London and Geneva informed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
